Explore impact of Variant_Classification categories

C. Savonen for ALSF CCDL

2020

Summary of Findings:

FoCR does not include Translation_Start_Site, Nonstop_Mutation or Splice_Site in the definition of nonsynonymous mutations but maftools does. See these GitHub comments. This notebook explores how ofte those categories come up so we can know whether this will influence downstream analyses. This addresses part 2 of this OpenPBTA issue

Usage

If both run_caller_consensus_analysis-tcga.sh and run_caller_consensus_analysis-pbta.sh have been run, you can run this command to run this notebook:

Rscript -e "rmarkdown::render("explore_var_class_discrepancies.Rmd", clean = TRUE)

Declare Variant_Classification definitions

# These are Friends of Cancer Research included
focr_nonsynonymous <- c(
  "Missense_Mutation",
  "Frame_Shift_Del",
  "In_Frame_Ins",
  "Frame_Shift_Ins",
  "Nonsense_Mutation",
  "In_Frame_Del"
)

# These are included in maftools definition, but not FoCR
discrepant_classes <- c(
  "Translation_Start_Site",
  "Nonstop_Mutation",
  "Splice_Site"
)

# All other variant classes are considered synonymous by both mafools and FoCR

Data wrangling

Summarize each dataset by these Variant_Classification definitions.

Do this for PBTA data:

pbta_summarize_syn_df <- tcga_df %>%
  dplyr::mutate(var_def = dplyr::case_when(
    Variant_Classification %in% discrepant_classes ~ "maftools_only",
    Variant_Classification %in% focr_nonsynonymous ~ "nonsynonymous",
    TRUE ~ "synonymous"
  )) %>%
  # Group and summarize
  dplyr::group_by(Variant_Classification, var_def) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(counts = dplyr::n())
`summarise()` regrouping output by 'Variant_Classification' (override with `.groups` argument)

Repeat same steps for TCGA data.

tcga_summarize_syn_df <- tcga_df %>%
  dplyr::mutate(var_def = dplyr::case_when(
    Variant_Classification %in% discrepant_classes ~ "maftools_only",
    Variant_Classification %in% focr_nonsynonymous ~ "nonsynonymous",
    TRUE ~ "synonymous"
  )) %>%
  # Group and summarize
  dplyr::group_by(Variant_Classification, var_def) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(counts = dplyr::n())
`summarise()` regrouping output by 'Variant_Classification' (override with `.groups` argument)

Lets make this into one dataset for convenience.

summarized_df <- dplyr::bind_rows(list(pbta = pbta_summarize_syn_df, tcga = tcga_summarize_syn_df),
  .id = "dataset"
) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  dplyr::mutate(var_def = as.factor(var_def))

Barplot of Variant Classification

summarized_df %>%
  ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(
    x = forcats::fct_reorder(Variant_Classification, as.numeric(var_def)),
    y = counts,
    fill = var_def
  )) +
  ggplot2::theme_classic() +
  ggplot2::geom_bar(
    position = "dodge", stat = "identity"
  ) +
  ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  ggplot2::xlab("") +
  ggplot2::ylab("Number of mutations") +
  colorblindr::scale_fill_OkabeIto() +
  ggplot2::facet_wrap(~dataset)

Summarize by definition inclusion/exclusion.

summarized_df %>%
  dplyr::group_by(var_def, dataset) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(total_count = sum(counts)) %>%
  ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(
    x = var_def,
    y = total_count,
    fill = var_def
  )) +
  ggplot2::theme_classic() +
  ggplot2::geom_bar(
    position = "dodge", stat = "identity"
  ) +
  ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  ggplot2::xlab("") +
  ggplot2::ylab("Number of TCGA mutations") +
  colorblindr::scale_fill_OkabeIto() +
